# --- secrets / credentials: NEVER commit ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.keystore
keystore/
id_rsa*
wallet*.json
*.secret
secrets.json

# --- rust (verifier) ---
/target/
**/target/

# --- foundry (contracts) ---
out/
cache/
contracts/out/
contracts/cache/
# dry-run simulations are local-only noise (no tx ever landed); the REAL broadcast record
# (broadcast/<script>/<chainid>/run-*.json) is kept as public on-chain deploy provenance.
**/dry-run/

# --- node / typescript (agent + web) ---
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
dist/
build/
.next/
*.tsbuildinfo

# --- verdict journal (design §5a) ---
# The DEFAULT journal `verify-tx` appends to (beside the spine) is a transient, local working file --
# ad-hoc runs append to it, so it is not committed. The CANONICAL demo journal the committed LEDGER.md
# is generated from lives at demo/proofagent.demo.journal and IS tracked (settlement-truth provenance).
/proofagent.journal
proofagent.journal
!demo/proofagent.demo.journal

# --- logs / os / editor ---
*.log
npm-debug.log*
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- generated full-stack evidence artifacts (regenerate locally; not tracked) ---
# The DURABLE evidence is demo/EVIDENCE_FULLSTACK_0G.md (tracked). The rendered PDF, the headless
# dashboard screenshot, and the one-shot generator scratch are local artifacts, not committed --
# mirroring demo/video/ (the build scripts are tracked; the rendered .mp4 is not).
demo/*.pdf
demo/__pycache__/
demo/_*.py
demo/_*.mjs
demo/_*.png
